92#define SET_VAR(group, variable, value) do { \
93 if (!compareEqual(group->variable, value)) \
94 group.access().variable = value; \
95 } while (0)
96
97#define SET_NESTED_VAR(group, parentVariable, variable, value) do { \
98 if (!compareEqual(group->parentVariable->variable, value)) \
99 group.access().parentVariable.access().variable = value; \
100 } while (0)
101
102#define SET_BORDERVALUE_COLOR(group, variable, value) do { \
103 if (!compareEqual(group->variable.color(), value)) \
104 group.access().variable.setColor(value); \
105 } while (0)

2064inline bool RenderStyle::NonInheritedFlags::hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId pseudo) const
2065{
2066 ASSERT(pseudo > PseudoId::None);
2067 ASSERT(pseudo < PseudoId::FirstInternalPseudoId);
2068 return pseudoBits & (1 << (static_cast<unsigned>(pseudo) - 1 /* PseudoId::None */));
2069}

2071inline void RenderStyle::NonInheritedFlags::setHasPseudoStyles(PseudoIdSet pseudoIdSet)
2072{
2073 ASSERT(pseudoIdSet);
2074 ASSERT((pseudoIdSet.data() & static_cast<unsigned>(PseudoId::PublicPseudoIdMask)) == pseudoIdSet.data());
2075 pseudoBits |= pseudoIdSet.data() >> 1; // Shift down as we do not store a bit for PseudoId::None.
2076}

2104inline int adjustForAbsoluteZoom(int value, const RenderStyle& style)
2105{
2106 double zoomFactor = style.effectiveZoom();
2107 if (zoomFactor == 1)
2108 return value;
2109 // Needed because computeLengthInt truncates (rather than rounds) when scaling up.
2110 if (zoomFactor > 1) {
2111 if (value < 0)
2112 value--;
2113 else
2114 value++;
2115 }
2116
2117 return roundForImpreciseConversion<int>(value / zoomFactor);
2118}
2119
2120inline float adjustFloatForAbsoluteZoom(float value, const RenderStyle& style)
2121{
2122 return value / style.effectiveZoom();
2123}

2125inline LayoutUnit adjustLayoutUnitForAbsoluteZoom(LayoutUnit value, const RenderStyle& style)
2126{
2127 return LayoutUnit(value / style.effectiveZoom());
2128}
